{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9e8d228e-da52-4dbe-be6a-439a997096a7","content":"\n\nWith Microsoft.Testing.Platform, the options change names. The equivalent command is:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test \\\n  -- \\\n  --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\nKey mappings:\n\n| VSTest | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|\n| `--filter` | `--filter` (same syntax) |\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `--hangdump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\nNote the `--` separator — everything after it is forwarded to the testing platform. You'll also need the `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` and `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` NuGet packages in your test project.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1d4c76af-015e-4ed7-8035-415473c7328e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing infrastructure, not a code change request.\n\nLet me provide the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n\nKey differences:\n- `--filter` → `--filter` (same)\n- `--logger trx` → `--report-trx` \n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` → `--collect-coverage` with Microsoft.CodeCoverage, or you use a different mechanism\n- `--blame-crash` → `--crashdump`\n\n\n- `--blame-hang` → `--hangdump`\n- `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` → `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\nWith .NET 8, `dotnet test` can work with Microsoft.Testing.Platform, though the exact invocation depends on how the test project is configured—you might use `dotnet run` or the built executable directly, or rely on the test adapter integration if available.\n\nWith Microsoft.Testing.Platform, the test project compiles to an executable that you can run directly with flags like `--filter`, `--report-trx`, `--coverage`, `--crashdump`, and `--hangdump`, or invoke through `dotnet test` as a wrapper. The command-line options map fairly directly: `--filter` stays the same, `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx`, and code coverage collection uses `--report-coverage` instead of the older `--collect` syntax. Writing command examples...","outputTokens":1075},"id":"ca3d600c-2c2b-45d3-8991-c232584ce0f8","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:52:01.296Z","parentId":"9c6e2330-698b-4561-a879-22a66798e683"}
